1. Problem Defination
   Build an ML model that classifies messages (SMS/Email) as Spam or Ham (Not Spam) using NLP techniques and classical machine 
   learning algorithms.
2. Data Collection
   Load dataset (CSV format)
   Common columns:
         text / Email → message content
         label / Category → ham/spam
3. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
   Data Shape
   Missing values
   Class distribution
   Word count / message length
   Visualizations
4. Data Cleaning & Preprocessing
   Applying NLP text-cleaning steps:
   Lowercasing
   Remove extra spaces
   Remove numbers
   Remove punctuation
5. Train–Test Split
6. Feature Extraction (TF-IDF)
7. Model Building
   Train different ML models:
   Logistic Regression
   Naive Bayes
   SVM
   Random Forest
   Decision Tree
   
